02:03:45.480 --> 02:03:52.200
[Guest]: she said you just write and I was a I was just 26 27 I think and then they got my photograph

02:03:52.200 --> 02:03:58.640
[Guest]: my my mug photo for an article first appeared in a European newspaper not in any of the

02:03:58.640 --> 02:04:03.080
[Guest]: Indian newspapers and they were so happy and then they called me for a radio debate like

02:04:03.080 --> 02:04:07.280
[Guest]: others and then I just explained my ideas and they were so surprised that I know so

02:04:07.280 --> 02:04:12.000
[Guest]: much of English literature without realizing that we had we were only exposed to Shakespeare

02:04:12.000 --> 02:04:18.440
[Guest]: and Beckett and Yeats and Joyce all of that so so so I mean I was a small hit you know

02:04:18.440 --> 02:04:24.160
[Guest]: I mean when I was there with them so Caroline Walsh and they were so welcoming they took

02:04:24.160 --> 02:04:29.560
[Guest]: you home and they she was so happy with that argument she took me home and her husband

02:04:29.560 --> 02:04:33.480
[Guest]: was a novelist so she said he's made this argument I'm getting him to write and then

02:04:33.480 --> 02:04:37.960
[Guest]: she took then there was another person called Paddy Woodworth who was in the foreign desk

02:04:37.960 --> 02:04:44.260
[Guest]: and he was very familiar with the Basque thing you know when he was very so he was very interested

02:04:44.260 --> 02:04:50.320
[Guest]: in this argument and then they got me to write a piece on Rajkumar had been kidnapped by

02:04:50.320 --> 02:04:55.280
[Guest]: Virappan here and that was a completely they didn't know how to understand the whole thing

